OL,3,CHead of Southport attacker's former
OL,4,Cschool felt 'sense of dread'
OL,6,FHe returned to the school in December
OL,7,Fthat year when he assaulted another
OL,8,Fstudent with a hockey stick and was
OL,9,Ffound to have a knife in his bag.
OL,11,FMs Hodson, who was acting head teacher
OL,12,Fwhen AR was at the pupil referral
OL,13,Funit, said: "I was aware he had taken
OL,14,Fknives in to school and I was worried
OL,15,Fthat he was going to bring something
OL,16,Fto our school and in the end he
OL,17,Fdidn't, he went to the Range and did
OL,18,Fit, but that is what I feared was
OL,19,Fgoing to happen to our school."
