OL,3,CHead of Southport attacker's former
OL,4,Cschool felt 'sense of dread'
OL,6,F"He was insistent that his views alone
OL,7,Fwere correct and everyone else was
OL,8,Fwrong. There was never any sense of
OL,9,Fremorse or accountability for his
OL,10,Factions."
OL,12,FShe told the inquiry: "His
OL,13,Finteractions with the other pupils
OL,14,Fwere very challenging and I was trying
OL,15,Fto work out exactly what was going on
OL,16,Fand trying to get help from other
OL,17,Fagencies to explain what we were
OL,18,Fdealing with really and get some help."
