OL,3,CHead of Southport attacker's former
OL,4,Cschool felt 'sense of dread'
OL,6,FMs Hodson said his parents were of the
OL,7,Fview he was a "good boy" who never did
OL,8,Fanything wrong and that "any issues
OL,9,Fwere someone else's fault".
OL,11,FBut, Ms Hodson said from January 2021
OL,12,Fshe had concerns AR's father may have
OL,13,Fbeen fearful of him and had lost
OL,14,Fcontrol of his son.
OL,16,FShe said school staff, who made three
OL,17,Freferrals about him to the
OL,18,FGovernment's anti-terror programme
OL,19,FPrevent, were concerned about him
OL,20,Fattacking his peers.
