OL,3,CHead of Southport attacker's former
OL,4,Cschool felt 'sense of dread'
OL,6,FIn her statement, she said: "We were
OL,7,Fconcerned that he was someone capable
OL,8,Fof being radicalised and that he was
OL,9,Fvulnerable.
OL,11,F"He was so socially isolated that I
OL,12,Fcould not conceive of the idea that he
OL,13,Fmight attack a group of strangers, let
OL,14,Falone young children.
OL,16,F"The tragic events are so far removed
OL,17,Ffrom what I would have associated AR
OL,18,Fwith in terms of risk."
